{
  "text": "Optimizing for rank-based metrics As rank-based evaluation metrics are now central to multiple research areas, their direct optimization has become of great interest to the community. Traditional approaches typically rely on different flavors of loss-augmented inference [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , or gradient approximation [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . These approaches often require solving a combinatorial problem as a subroutine where the nature of the problem is dependent on the particular rank-based metric. Consequently, efficient algorithms for these subproblems were proposed [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
  "correct_citation": {
